Holiday Calories don’t count! 🤪  We made sooo much 🦃🥘🥧 over the weekend. I loved my first time making pull-apart bread. It turns out so good! 🥰Never loved my own baked goods this much before 🤣 here is the recipe:
-fill each crescent roll with cheeses- I used an Italian mix 🇮🇹. You can shape the bread any way 
-brush the top with butter, top with fresh herbs and cranberries 
-bake at 375 for 20 minutes or until golden brown😋😍

24 hour ✈️ weekend getaway girls trip! 📍Big Island

✨Breakfast: @vibe.bigisland for a vegan restaurant with the best aesthetics in town! I am not vegan but always down to try new things! Blue majik algae latte & lavender latte is a must
Road-trip from East coast: Beaches near Hilo to West coast: Beaches near Kona
✨Punalu'u Black Sand Beach (TURTLES, SWIMMING AND SNORKELING spot)
✨Rainbow waterfall near Hilo
✨Kaumana Cave breathtaking view carved by lava! 25mi long (you need a flashlight, your cellphone light isn't strong enough go through the whole cave- and no slippers!) 
✨Lunch at @fshualalai 
✨ @greenwellfarms coffee tour: very informative and fun! History, plant facts 🌱, and they produce coffee for Starbucks! A place to check out!
✨Active volcano that's probably the most amazing thing we saw on this trip, and as soon as we left it became active again for the first time in almost 40 years 🤩so amazing

Save this if you ever visit the Big Island, HAWAII

Took my bestie of 11 years for a feast at @goofyhi. It's a tropical beachy open-air vibe. We were so impressed by their food quality! I think this is the best french toast I have ever had! Food recommendations: 
✨Hawaiian açaí bowl
✨Local bibimbap
✨French toast
✨Beef loco moco 
Drink recommendation:
✨Pina colada smoothie
✨Papaya smoothie
Save this place for your next Hawaii trip~It's one of the best spots to bring your bestie for brunch and mimosas🥰if you want a good seat definitely go there early! There will be a line😋

Want an amazing appetizer for your New Year’s Eve party?✨I got you👌🏼🥓Bacon Wrapped Asparagus🥓It’s easy to make and a total crowd pleaser with crispy bacon! And it pretty much goes with everything! The recipe is simple: 
1. Cook the bacon half-way (why? So the bacon is crispy without over cooking the asparagus!)
2. Wrap the bacon around the asparagus 
3. Air fry for 10 minutes at around 350 degrees (air fryer from @cenorthamerica ) 
4. Voilà! A tasty treat for any occasion 

What would you like to eat with this dish? ✨

Fresh year, fresh hair, fresh thoughts:
✨Don't try to change yourself to fit in. Instead,  be yourself and be kind- it attracts the right people in your life
✨Make goals not because everyone else made them, but because you are creating your own character
✨Make someone's day! It’s so important to make an impact on other people's lives. It can be one smile, one nice word… small things like that
✨Know that confidence is not the end of the journey- it’s an unexpected reward in the pursuit of your goals 
✨Whatever it is you're scared of doing, do it, and make your mistakes! We don't stop doing things because they’re wrong, We keep doing it until it's right. Failures dont make you a failure
✨Running away from any problem only increases the distance from the solution. Instead, sit down, pause, reflect and act; face to it, let it pass through you!🌞

What I’ve learned from my relationship of 11 years💖:

1. Different personalities can make things beautiful. You don’t need a partner with all the same hobbies as you. With balance you will see more of the world, as long as you share the same values.
2. Feeling good on the inside will reflect on the outside. Somebody wisely said: “if you aren’t happy with yourself, you can’t make anyone else happy.” Learn how to love yourself and be happy first!
3. Learn from disagreements and arguments. The more you analyze the root of the problem, the better the relationship will be. Learning about each other is essential.
4. Give each other space, but when together give yourselves the opportunity to open up. Have a date, tell stories or just talk to each other. It’s your quality time and you need to spend it well.
5. Support each other against problems- don’t make problems for each other. You need to understand the value of healthy criticism and that you’re on the same team. Remember: we are all human and make mistakes. Always show support. 2022 I have deeply understand tomorrow is never promised, be grateful and appreciate the people who choose to stay in your life❤️

Getting ready for Chinese New Year🐰 🏮
6 things you needs to know about the CNY red envelope 🧧 
1. It needs to contain new, clean cash
2. The amount can never include the number 4- which in Chinese sounds the same as “death”. Can give amounts with 6 or 8, which are lucky numbers 
3. People not only give 🧧 on CNY, but also occasions like birthdays, weddings, or funerals in some places 
4. The quantity of money depends on your relationship- closer relative means more money
5. The envelope needs to be red! It can’t be another color
6. Don’t put coins in the envelope- unless chocolate coins for the kids!

Here are the things you can do on international women's day:

✨Send your female friends/family/bloggers a love message or a like to their post, building connections and showing love

✨Support more women-owned businesses

✨Donate to a women's organization

✨Read a book by a female author

✨Be a cheerleader and supporter for your female friends

When life throws you lemons🍋... I know we all hear that happiness is all that matters; however, life is life and sometimes things get out of your hands. Shit happens that may be against your intentions, but once we accept that, it's a very natural portion of life. Just like pleasure is.  I saw a video a while ago- there's a saying "our ability to suffer will determine the quality of our life" and I can't agree more. Meanwhile, pay attention to who you are in the middle of it. Pay attention to how it forced you to heal to grow and remember this brand new version of yourself that is still standing tall coming out of it, caz that is the biggest gift this life is able to give you. constant growth and elevation🤜🏼🤛🏽! If you can't accept the shit life throws at you, you won't be able to accept the gifts life gives you❤️happy weekend everyone🙌🏼outfit linked in my bio: https://liketk.it/45bdN @shop.ltk #liketoknowit

Hey, Insta fam! 🌊 Today, I want to take a moment to reflect on my journey from growing up in the city to finding my place in the tropical paradise of Hawaii.

Where I grew up, water sports were never a part of my life. While my friends effortlessly surf across the waves, I struggle to find my balance 🤣 and I take a different approach. Hawaii has taught me to embrace challenges and turn them into opportunities for growth. 

Hawaii offers so much more, so many ways to find yourself. I've embarked on stunning hikes to hidden waterfalls, where I can bask in the beauty of nature and cool off in refreshing pools, enjoyed endless breathtaking sunsets, island hopping, amazing restaurants, and friendships for which I am forever grateful! 🌈It really has taught me about finding joy in the things that truly resonate, even if it means taking a different path from my friends.

I hope my story inspires you to embrace your individuality , follow your passions,  wherever it may take you. Remember, it's not about comparing ourselves to others; it's about discovering what makes us come alive and diving headfirst into those experiences! 💫

Fun fact💁🏻‍♀️! I never thought I'd be living in swimsuits this much🤣then the beach life has taken over. I've embraced a lifestyle that celebrates self-love, body positivity, and the joy of soaking up the sun, and everyday is a reminder that beauty comes in all forms, and true confidence radiates from within🫶🏼

I'm an extroverted person, so I'm often asked, "Why are you always so happy?" Well, 95% time I am! The answer is simple—staying true to myself and not taking life or people's opinions too seriously. 💃

Growing up, I encountered so many voices telling me how I should behave, what was expected of me, and how to fit into certain roles. But you know what? I made a choice to be faithful to my own unique personality. I refused to let others define who I should be, and that decision is the best decision ever in my life. 

Just as important is not taking others' opinions personally. We always encounter a lot of judgmental people. But here's the secret: other people's opinions don't reflect your worth. Let go of what doesn't serve you. I always believe God closes one door but will open one window. 🫶🏼

I realize now that social media can trigger anxiety and negative thoughts. Many people fall into the comparison trap, feeling like they're not good enough or their lives aren't as glamorous as those they see online. But the truth is: your worth and happiness aren't defined by likes, followers, or anyone else's feed. By better recognizing that I've been able to navigate social media with a healthier mindset, focusing on genuine connections and uplifting content. 💪

2023 has been an exciting journey, with steps towards building my business and taking life in my own hands. Here are 10 things I’ve learned along the way that can hopefully help you in the next year:

✨Stay focused: Don’t get distracted by what others are doing, you can do things your own way! You are the creator of your own brand.
✨If it makes you happy and you love what you do, it doesn’t have to make sense to anyone else. 
✨People come and go, find your people and never take them for granted. 🫶🏼
✨Invest in your personal development. You will always be learning and "unlearning"
✨You can plan lots of things but by the end of the day always clap for what has worked for you
✨Customers are the heartbeat of the business. Always be grateful for each and every one who places their trust in you🫶🏼
✨You can do anything but not everything, Build a team and bring the best of them! Love is the answer.
✨Always remember to take time for yourself to recharge. Life is all about balance
✨Not everybody understands you, and that's ok! 
✨The more you believe in yourself, the less you need others to.🤗

Have a great day everyone🫶🏼
